item.title: CVE-2017-1711|2024-09-17T04:29:16.940Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM iNotes 8.5 and 9.0 SUService can be misguided into running malicious code from a DLL masquerading as a windows DLL in the temp directory. IBM X-Force ID: 134532.

item.title: CVE-2017-1714|2024-09-17T02:56:31.561Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM Notes and Domino NSD 8.5 and 9.0 could allow an authenticated local user without administrative privileges to gain System privilege. IBM X-Force ID: 134633.

item.title: CVE-2018-1411|2024-09-17T01:51:25.769Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM Notes Diagnostics (IBM Client Application Access and IBM Notes) could allow a local user to execute commands on the system. By crafting a command line sent via the shared memory IPC, which could be tricked into executing an executable chosen by the attacker. IBM X-Force ID: 138710.
